dia]]\n| \n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wisden.com/almanack/smriti-mandhana-leading-women-cricketer-wisden-2019|title=Smriti Mandhana: Wisden's Leading Cricketer In The World 2018|date=2019-04-10|website=Wisden|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | 2019\n| [[File:Ellyse Perry.jpg|frameless|100px]]\n| {{sortname|Ellyse|Perry}}\n| [[Australia women's national cricket team|Australia]]\n|\n| <ref name=ell>{{Cite web | url = https://www.wisden.com/almanack/leading-woman-cricketer-in-the-world-in-2019-ellyse-perry | title = Leading Woman Cricketer in the World in 2019: Ellyse Perry | website = WIsden | accessdate = 2020-04-08 | date = 2020-04-08}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[ICC Women's Cricketer of the Year]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Wisden awards}}\n{{International women's cricket}}\n\n\n[[Category:Cricket awards and rankings]]\n[[Category:Wisden]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Women's cricket-related lists]]\n", "name_user": "The Rambling Man", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wisden_Leading_Woman_Cricketer_in_the_World"}
{"title_page": "We Are Here (collective)", "text_new": "{{short description|Human rights campaign of migrants in Amsterdam}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name                = We Are Here\n| native_name         = Wij Zijn Hier\n| native_name_lang    = NL\n| image               = File:20180428BannerWeAreHere.jpg\n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = Banner at 2018 demonstration\n| caption             = Banner at 2018 demonstration\n| map                 = File:Amsterdamse stadsdelen 2010.png\n| map_size            = \n| map_alt             = Boroughs of Amsterdam\n| map_caption         = Boroughs of Amsterdam\n| logo                = \n| logo_size           = \n| logo_alt            = \n| logo_caption        = \n| abbreviation        = WZH\n| nickname            = \n| formation           = {{start date and age|2012|09|04}}\n| founding_location   = Garden of Diakonie, Amsterdam\n| location            = Amsterdam\n| purpose             = Rights for migrants\n| methods             = Campaigning, Demonstrations, Direct Action, Squatting\n| website             = {{URL|wijzijnhier.org}}\n}}\n'''We Are Here''' ([[Dutch (language)|Dutch]]: '''Wij Zijn Hier''') is a [[collective]] of migrants based in [[Amsterdam]], the [[Netherlands]], which campaigns for human rights for its members and all undocumented migrants. The asylum seekers have in many cases had their applications to remain in the Netherlands denied but they either cannot go back or refuse to return to their country of origin. They ask for access to social services such as medical care and housing.\n\nThe group is constantly in flux as a result of individually precarious legal situations. Since its members refuse to use the [[homeless shelter]]s offered by the city of Amsterdam, which can only be used from 5 pm until 9 am, the collective has [[Squatting|squatted]] a chain of buildings in and around the city since 2012. Most buildings are quickly evicted, some have led to offshoot projects. The group is mostly composed of men originally from Africa, although there have also been women only occupations. There have been some successes, such as the Vluchtmaat, where a longterm deal was negotiated with the owner, and some longterm squats such as the Vluchtgarage, where [[Amsterdam city council]] tolerated the occupation. As of 2017, roughly one hundred people from the group had gained Dutch residence permits.\n\nBy 2018, the new council had pledged to set up 24 hour shelters for up to 500 undocumented migrants, but We Are Here stated it was against the shelters since they were only for a short time period and it disputed the plan to send asylum seekers back to their country of origin at the end of the project. The collective by this point had diversified into different subgroups occupying different buildings, such as a women-only group, a [[Swahili language]] group, and a group composed of people mainly from [[Ethiopia]], [[Eritrea]] and [[Sudan]].\n\n== Background ==\nRefugees seeking asylum in the Netherlands are assessed by the [[Immigration and Naturalisation Service (Netherlands)|Immigration and Naturalisation Service]] and then either gain residency or fail to do so, based on their documentary evidence. For some who have fled warzones, it is difficult to provide documents or other proof for their claim. If the refugees fail to be granted asylum, they are given temporary housing and have 28 days to leave. Some people fall into \"the asylum gap\" since they are unable to return to their country of origin, whilst others want to go back but cannot because they do not possess the required visas or identity documents. In 2016, it was estimated there were 35,000 undocumented migrants in the Netherlands. Without a residence permit they are denied access to social services such as healthcare and housing.<ref name=\"Limbo\">{{cite news |last1=Merks |first1=Kelly |title=Life in Limbo in the Netherlands |url=https://access-nl.org/features/life-in-limbo-in-nl/ |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Access Magazine |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711164915/https://access-nl.org/features/life-in-limbo-in-nl/ |archivedate=11 July 2019 |language=EN}}</ref><ref name=\"Brechtje\">{{cite news |last1=Keulen |first1=Brechtje |title=\u2018Wij zijn allemaal moe\u2019 |url=https://www.groene.nl/artikel/wij-zijn-allemaal-moe|accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Groene Amsterdammer |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712153050/https://www.groene.nl/artikel/wij-zijn-allemaal-moe |archivedate=12 July 2019 |language=NL}}</ref>\n\nThe migrants of the We Are Here [[collective]] had by the end of 2017 occupied over 30 buildings and parks.<ref name=\"Koops\">{{cite news |last1=Wolthuizen |first1=Josien |last2=Koops |first2=Ruben |title=We Are Here: Vijf jaar later nog geen stap verder |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-vijf-jaar-later-nog-geen-stap-verder~bdbdf167/ |accessdate=10 May 2019 |work=Parool |date=1 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510200206/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-vijf-jaar-later-nog-geen-stap-verder~bdbdf167/ |archive-date=10 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> They argue that they should have access to basic needs such as housing and healthcare. The city council of Amsterdam refuses to accede to their demands. Much of the dispute with the Council is that it only offers the so-called BBB service - Bed-Bath-Bread ([[Dutch (language)|Dutch]]: bed-bad-broodvoorziening), that is to say an overnight accommodation open from 5pm until 9am, which cannot be stayed in during the day. The migrants reject this offer as insufficient and say it is in any case often over-subscribed.<ref name=\"Koops\" /> The city council in turn says that its hands are tied by the policy of the [[Dutch Government]].<ref name=\"Karman-1\">{{cite news |last1=Karman |first1=Jasper |title=Havenstraat biedt iedereen hoop |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/havenstraat-biedt-iedereen-hoop~bbfc9f3d/ |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=6 December 2013 |language=NL |quote=Dat tot frustratie van de burgemeester en de gemeenteraad, die allebei graag meer wilden doen, maar moesten blijven herhalen dat niet Amsterdam, maar Den Haag over het asielbeleid gaat en dat de stad geen asielzoekers m\u00e1g opvangen. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705210244/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/havenstraat-biedt-iedereen-hoop~bbfc9f3d/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Therefore, We Are Here have chosen to [[Squatting|squat]] a number of buildings to live in. By 2019, the total had risen to over 50 squats according to the group's own count. The occupations are tracked on a map hosted on the We Are Here website.<ref name=\"Geschiedenis1\">{{cite web |title=Geschiedenis van Wij Zijn Hier |url=http://wijzijnhier.org/tijdslijn/geschiedenis-van-wij-zijn-hier/ |website=We Are Here |accessdate=12 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705212427/https://wijzijnhier.org/tijdslijn/geschiedenis-van-wij-zijn-hier/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nWe Are Here is mostly composed of men originally from Africa. In some occupations, it was men only, for example the Vluchgarage.<ref name=\"BBB-meer-2\">{{cite web |title=BED, BAD, BROOD EN M\u00c9\u00c9R\u2026 |url=https://vluchtverhalen.nl/we-are-here-wij-zijn-hier/ |website=Vluchtverhalen |accessdate=5 July 2019 |language=NL |quote=Het zijn alleen mannen, afkomstig uit vooral Afrikaanse en Arabische landen. |date=2017-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705210220/https://vluchtverhalen.nl/we-are-here-wij-zijn-hier/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, there have also been women only squats.<ref name=\"Stopera\">{{cite news |title=We Are Here-vrouwen demonstreren bij Stopera |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-vrouwen-demonstreren-bij-stopera~b1418ee91/ |accessdate=9 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=10 April 2018 |language=NL |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709215458/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-vrouwen-demonstreren-bij-stopera~b1418ee91/ |archive-date=9 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The group's membership changes often since people are often being deported or detained. Overall, representatives of the group estimated that over one hundred people had gained residence permits.<ref name=\"Koops\" /> For example, a spokesperson for the group, Khalid Jone, who escaped war in Sudan and had lived in the Netherlands for 16 years, was granted a residence permit in 2018.<ref name=\"Kieft\">{{cite news |last1=Kieft |first1=Tom |title=We Are Here-woordvoerder krijgt na 16 jaar verblijfsvergunning |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-woordvoerder-krijgt-na-16-jaar-verblijfsvergunning~b7a7df8c/ |quote=Toen hij dinsdag zijn email opende en las dat hem een verblijfsvergunning zou zijn toegekend, geloofde hij het niet. |accessdate=14 May 2019 |work=Parool |date=18 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510201146/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-woordvoerder-krijgt-na-16-jaar-verblijfsvergunning~b7a7df8c/ |archive-date=10 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The collective regularly makes demonstrations highlighting the plight of individuals.<ref name=\"Stopera\" /> It has also set up the We Are Here Academy, a scheme to offer university level qualifications for undocumented migrants.<ref>{{Cite book | url=https://books.google.com/?id=gsRlDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA54&lpg=PA54&dq=%22wij+zijn+hier%22+squatters+amsterdam#v=onepage&q=%22wij%20zijn%20hier%22%20squatters%20amsterdam&f=false |title = Solidarity and the 'Refugee Crisis' in Europe|isbn = 9783319918488|last1 = Agust\u00edn|first1 = \u00d3scar Garc\u00eda|last2 = J\u00f8rgensen|first2 = Martin Bak|date = 2018-07-19}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, a newly elected [[Amsterdam city council]], now controlled by a[[Centre-left politics|centre-left]] coalition of [[GroenLinks]], [[Democrats 66|D66]], [[Labour Party (Netherlands)|PvdA]] and [[Socialist Party (Netherlands)|SP]], decided to go against the will of the [[States General of the Netherlands|Parliament]] and to set up a 24-hour [[Homeless shelter|shelter]] for homeless failed asylum seekers.<ref name=\"probeert\">{{cite news |last1=van Unen |first1=David |title=We Are Here probeert tevergeefs nieuw pand te kraken |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-probeert-tevergeefs-nieuw-pand-te-kraken~bed3bff7/ |accessdate=10 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=3 June 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510193834/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-probeert-tevergeefs-nieuw-pand-te-kraken~bed3bff7/?utm_source=link&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=shared%20content&utm_content=free |archivedate=10 May 2019 |quote=Het nieuwe college van Groenlinks, D66, PvdA en SP wil, ondanks weerstand uit Den Haag, 24-uursopvang gaan aanbieden voor de veelal uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers van We Are Here. De groep is echter niet van plan daar gebruik van te maken, herhaalt Jone zondag nog eens.}}</ref> However, We Are Here as a group announced it would not make use of the shelter, since it would only exist for a maximum time of eighteen months and (as part of the proposal) afterwards migrants would have to return to their country of origin. Since We Are Here was set up for people unable to return to their motherland, a spokesman said the plan offered no real solution.<ref name=\"probeert2\">{{cite news |last1=van Unen |first1=David |title=We Are Here probeert tevergeefs nieuw pand te kraken |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-probeert-tevergeefs-nieuw-pand-te-kraken~bed3bff7/ |accessdate=10 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=3 June 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510193834/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-probeert-tevergeefs-nieuw-pand-te-kraken~bed3bff7/?utm_source=link&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=shared%20content&utm_content=free |archivedate=10 May 2019 |quote=De nieuwe opvang biedt voor maximaal anderhalf jaar een oplossing. Daarna moeten asielzoekers meewerken aan een terugkeer naar het land van herkomst, terwijl dat juist niet is wat We Are Here wil. Jone vreest dat hij en leden van z'n groep dan na zes maanden terug de straat op moeten of vastgezet worden.}}</ref> In March 2019, the council announced seven prospective sites for its plan to set up shelters for undocumented migrants. It was considering up to 23 sites, with around 30 beds at each. The cities of Rotterdam, Utrecht, Groningen and Eindhoven stated that they were all also looking for sites.<ref name=\"opvang\">{{cite news |last1=Raap |first1=Rebekka |last2=Hielkema |first2=David |title=Dit zijn de 7 mogelijke locaties voor opvang van asielzoekers |url=https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/dit-zijn-de-7-mogelijke-locaties-voor-opvang-van-asielzoekers~b5e9e7d2/ |accessdate=10 July 2019 |date=12 March 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510193847/https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/dit-zijn-de-7-mogelijke-locaties-voor-opvang-van-asielzoekers~b5e9e7d2/ |archivedate=10 May 2019 |language=NL}}</ref>\n\n[[Femke Halsema]] (previously [[parliamentary leader]] of [[GroenLinks]]) started serving a six-year term as [[Mayor of Amsterdam]] in July 2018. In 2019, she discussed making the enforcement of the [[Dutch squatting ban]] tougher and suggested that the immigration police could be employed to stop the We Are Here collective squatting. GroenLinks asked for clarification since the tradition in Amsterdam is that illegal migrants are not searched for by the police.<ref name=\"Koops-Halsema\">{{cite news |last1=Koops |first1=Ruben |title=Halsema: \u2018Illegalen die geen strafbare feiten plegen hebben niets te vrezen\u2019 |url=https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/halsema-illegalen-die-geen-strafbare-feiten-plegen-hebben-niets-te-vrezen~b4613d26/ |accessdate=27 December 2019 |work=Het Parool |date=18 December 2019 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/CHKjh |archivedate=14 March 2020 |language=nl-NL |quote=GroenLinks had om opheldering gevraagd, nadat Halsema eerder dit jaar zei dat zij de vreemdelingenpolitie wil inschakelen tegen de asielactivisten van We Are Here [...] GroenLinks was bang dat de burgemeester daarmee afscheid nam van de Amsterdamse traditie dat op illegale vreemdelingen in principe niet gejaagd wordt door de veiligheidsdiensten. |url-status=live }}</ref> Halsema stated that if We Are Here members did nothing wrong they had nothing to fear, but that squatting was a criminal offence. GroenLinks stated it was troubled by this position.<ref name=\"Koops-Halsema2\">{{cite news |last1=Koops |first1=Ruben |title=Halsema: \u2018Illegalen die geen strafbare feiten plegen hebben niets te vrezen\u2019 |url=https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/halsema-illegalen-die-geen-strafbare-feiten-plegen-hebben-niets-te-vrezen~b4613d26/ |accessdate=27 December 2019 |work=Het Parool |date=18 December 2019 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/CHKjh |archivedate=14 March 2020 |language=nl-NL |quote=Maar Halsema wees erop dat We Are Here regelmatig de wet breekt, onder meer door bewoonde panden te kraken. \u201cIllegalen die niets hebben gedaan worden niet in detentie geplaatst,\u201d beloofde Halsema. \u201cMaar ook voor We Are Here geldt dat, als er strafbare feiten worden gepleegd, er aanhoudingen volgen en de juridische procedure moet worden doorlopen. Vreemdelingendetentie kan dan de consequentie zijn,\u201d zei Halsema. [...] Onder de achterban van GroenLinks was grote onrust ontstaan om de uitspraken van de burgemeester, zei raadslid Femke Roosma. |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n== Significant occupations ==\n=== 2012\u20132017 ===\nWe Are Here coalesced as a group in 2012, when a small number of asylum seekers whose claims had been rejected decided to make a protest camp at the garden of the Diakonie on the [[Nieuwe Herengracht]] in the [[Grachtengordel]] in central Amsterdam.<ref name=\"29ste-1\">{{cite news |last1=Wolthuizen |first1=Josien |title=Arrestatie bij ontruiming 29ste onderkomen Wij Zijn Hier |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~b276a1a0/ |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Parool |date=17 November 2017 |language=NL |quote=In september van dat jaar sloegen drie asielzoekers uit Eritrea een tentje op in de achtertuin van de Diakonie op de Nieuwe Herengracht |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620222010/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~b276a1a0/ |archive-date=20 June 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> More migrants joined the protest, which then moved location to Notweg in [[Osdorp]]. The camp swelled to 130 people and received national media attention. The camp was evicted on 30 November. Everyone was arrested and some people were held in foreign detention ([[Dutch (language)|Dutch]]: vreemdelingendetentie).<ref name=\"BBB-meer-1\">{{cite web |title=BED, BAD, BROOD EN M\u00c9\u00c9R\u2026 |url=https://vluchtverhalen.nl/we-are-here-wij-zijn-hier/ |website=VLUCHTVERHALEN |publisher=Vluchtverhalen |accessdate=5 July 2019 |quote=Het aantal bewoners in het tentenkamp in Osdorp groeit tot ongeveer 130. De gemeente Amsterdam weet zich niet goed raad met de situatie. De actievoerders krijgen veel steun vanuit de bevolking en de Protestantse Diaconie, maar worden ook bedreigd vanuit rechts-radicale hoek. Vanuit Den Haag wordt druk uitgeoefend de vreemdelingen te wijzen op hun \u2018vertrekplicht\u2018.  Uiteindelijk geeft burgemeester Eberhard van der Laan op 30 november 2012 de politie opdracht het kamp te ontruimen. Vele mensen worden gearresteerd. Een tiental verdwijnt in vreemdelingendetentie. |date=2017-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705210220/https://vluchtverhalen.nl/we-are-here-wij-zijn-hier/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAfter a few nights staying at the Vondelpark Bunker and [[OT301]], the group squatted an empty church in [[Bos en Lommer]]. This became known as the Vluchtkerk, a portmanteau of the Dutch words for migrant ([[Dutch (language)|Dutch]]: vluchteling) and church ([[Dutch (language)|Dutch]]: kerk). This began the tradition of giving every new location a nickname, by adding 'Vlucht' to the type of place. The Vluchtkerk again generated a lot of media attention in the Netherlands.<ref name=\"Rechten\">{{cite news |last1=Steenhuis |first1=Peter Henk |title=Wie geen nationaliteit heeft, heeft geen rechten |url=https://www.trouw.nl/nieuws/wie-geen-nationaliteit-heeft-heeft-geen-rechten~b3d9ceed/ |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Trouw |date=18 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712093803/https://www.trouw.nl/nieuws/wie-geen-nationaliteit-heeft-heeft-geen-rechten~b3d9ceed/ |archive-date=12 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Bescherming\">{{cite news |last1=van Wijk |first1=Lieke |last2=van Wijnbergen |first2=Lucille |title='Illegaliteit strafbaar? Zo criminaliseer je groep die bescherming nodig heeft' |url=https://www.volkskrant.nl/columns-opinie/illegaliteit-strafbaar-zo-criminaliseer-je-groep-die-bescherming-nodig-heeft~b1e2f38b/ |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Volkskrant |date=13 March 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712093715/https://www.volkskrant.nl/columns-opinie/illegaliteit-strafbaar-zo-criminaliseer-je-groep-die-bescherming-nodig-heeft~b1e2f38b/ |archive-date=12 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Celebrities such as popstar [[Anouk (singer)|Anouk]] made solidarity performances.<ref name=\"Anouk\">{{cite news |last1=Redactie |title=Weblog Vluchtkerk: kerst met Anouk en PVV met een geweer |url=https://www.bndestem.nl/overig/weblog-vluchtkerk-kerst-met-anouk-en-pvv-met-een-geweer~ac86971f/ |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=BN DeStem |date=26 December 2012 |language=NL |quote=Afrikaanse muziek is het natuurlijk niet, maar de titel van een van de nummers die Anouk op kerstavond zong tijdens haar verrassingsoptreden in De Vluchtkerk was wel toepasselijk:'I don't wanna hurt no more' ....... |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703133132/https://www.bndestem.nl/overig/weblog-vluchtkerk-kerst-met-anouk-en-pvv-met-een-geweer~ac86971f/ |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> \n\nThe Vluchtkerk was occupied until 31 May 2013. Mayor of Amsterdam [[Eberhard van der Laan]] then asked the group to leave a building they had squatted on the Weteringschans and the council offered the migrants the possibility to stay in a former prison for 6 months. Many people refused, citing bad prior experiences of prisons, but 75 others took the opportunity and it became known as the Vluchthaven.<ref name=\"Eigenraam-1\">{{cite news |last1=Eigenraam |first1=Anouk |title=Amsterdamse asielzoekers kraken nieuw pand |url=https://www.nrc.nl/nieuws/2013/12/13/amsterdamse-asielzoekers-kraken-nieuw-pand-a1428873 |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=NRC |language=NL |quote=Burgemeester Eberhard van der Laan eiste dat de groep uit dit pand zou vertrekken. Ongeveer 75 anderen accepteerden het bod van de gemeente Amsterdam en kregen zo onderdak in een voormalige gevangenis aan de Havenstraat. Ze mogen daar een halfjaar blijven.}}</ref><ref name=\"Karman-2\">{{cite news |last1=Karman |first1=Jasper |title=Havenstraat biedt iedereen hoop |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/havenstraat-biedt-iedereen-hoop~bbfc9f3d/ |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=6 December 2013 |language=NL |quote=Daarnaast riep ook het gebouw zelf weerstand op: bij de aanblik van de gevangenis hadden velen vervelende associaties. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705210244/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/havenstraat-biedt-iedereen-hoop~bbfc9f3d/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Only migrants who signed up with the Dutch Refugee Council were eligible to stay there. To break down the statistics produced at the end of the social experiment, of the 165 people who stayed in the prison, only three returned to their country of origin (three more planned to), only 12 successfully gained residency, one person died and the largest number (38) was formed by those still gathering documents for their asylum process. In terms of country of origin, the largest numbers of people were from Somalia (48), Eritrea (31) and Ethiopia (28).<ref name=\"NewWay\">{{cite news |last1=Devaney |first1=Beulah Maud |title=The city of Amsterdam has come up with a new way to help its refugee population |url=https://www.citymetric.com/city-amsterdam-has-come-new-way-help-its-refugee-population |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=City Metric |date=12 September 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171210215747/http://www.citymetric.com/city-amsterdam-has-come-new-way-help-its-refugee-population |archivedate=10 December 2017 |language=EN}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 December 2013, a building in Amsterdam Zuid Oost was occupied by a group of 90 migrants and their supporters. It was a derelict parking garage with offices attached, which became known as the Vluchtgarage.<ref name=\"Eigenraam-2\">{{cite news |last1=Eigenraam |first1=Anouk |title=Amsterdamse asielzoekers kraken nieuw pand |url=https://www.nrc.nl/nieuws/2013/12/13/amsterdamse-asielzoekers-kraken-nieuw-pand-a1428873 |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=NRC |language=NL |quote=De uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers die sinds begin december door Amsterdam zwerven, hebben vandaag een nieuw pand gekraakt, zo laten ze in een verklaring weten. Het gaat om de groep van negentig asielzoekers die niet in aanmerking kwam voor opvang in een voormalige gevangenis. }}</ref> It was occupied until April 2015. In August 2014, a Somali man called Nassir Guuleed died at the squat. A few days later, Ibrahim Tour\u00e9 from [[C\u00f4te d'Ivoire]] suffered a brain haemorrhage and broken vertebra when he fell off a stairway. Police and ambulance services refused to enter the building (fearing the presence of asbestos despite the city having found none in an inspection earlier that same the day), so the severely injured man was carried to the ambulance.<ref name=\"Hurt\">{{cite news |last1=Hokstam |first1=Marvin |title=Politics Asylum seeker hurt in Amsterdam squat |url=https://nltimes.nl/2014/08/27/asylum-seeker-hurt-amsterdam-squat |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=Dutch News |date=27 August 2014 |language=EN}}</ref>[[Fred Teeven]], [[Undersecretary]] for [[Ministry of Security and Justice (Netherlands)|Security and Justice]] announced his intention to evict the Vluchtgarage in January 2015. At this point there were around 100 people living there.<ref name=\"Teeven-ontruimd\">{{cite news |title=Vluchtgarage Amsterdam wordt ontruimd |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2013173-vluchtgarage-amsterdam-wordt-ontruimd.html |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=NOS |date=13 January 2015 |language=NL |quote=De ruim honderd uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers die worden opgevangen in de Vluchtgarage in Amsterdam, moeten het gebouw uit. Staatssecretaris Teeven van Justitie laat weten dat de oude garage in Zuidoost ontruimd zal worden. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705204427/https://nos.nl/artikel/2013173-vluchtgarage-amsterdam-wordt-ontruimd.html |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Following the eviction in April 2015, people camped on land in the [[De Pijp]] neighbourhood but were moved on by the council.<ref name=\"Dismantle\">{{cite news |title=Amsterdam tells refugees to dismantle camp on building land |url=https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2015/04/amsterdam-tells-refugees-to-dismantle-camp-on-building-land/ |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Dutch News |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622024941/https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2015/04/amsterdam-tells-refugees-to-dismantle-camp-on-building-land/ |archivedate=22 June 2019 |language=EN}}</ref>\n\nBy 2015, We Are Here was composed in total of around 225 migrants from about 15 countries. As well as occupying several buildings, they regularly made demonstrations demanding rights. The council's response remained the same, namely that it could only offer a hostel that opened at 5pm and closed at 9am, otherwise it would be contravening the policy laid down by [[States General of the Netherlands|Parliament]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Drummond |first1=Lyn |title=Asylum seekers squat empty buildings while waiting for Netherlands approval |url=https://newint.org/features/web-exclusive/2015/10/30/asylum-seekers-wait-for-netherlands-approval |accessdate=10 July 2019 |work=New Internationalist |date=30 October 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710080427/https://newint.org/features/web-exclusive/2015/10/30/asylum-seekers-wait-for-netherlands-approval |archivedate=10 July 2019 |language=EN |quote=NI}}</ref>\nAt each squat, the collective was helped out by local people who donated things. If something was needed, a request was made on the website or on Facebook. Often things were scavenged from the street.<ref>{{Cite book | url=https://books.google.com/?id=r2FTCwAAQBAJ&pg=PT82&lpg=PT82&dq=ontruiming+%22wij+zijn+hier%22+amsterdam#v=onepage&q=ontruiming%20%22wij%20zijn%20hier%22%20amsterdam&f=false |title = EU@Amsterdam: Een stedelijke raad|isbn = 9789048531448|last1 = Mamadouh|first1 = Virginie|last2 = Wageningen|first2 = Anne van|date = 2016-01-05}}</ref> The Vluchtmaat was occupied in 2015 by 40 migrants mainly from [[Ethiopia]] and [[Eritrea]]. The name came from running together the words, Vluchtelingen (migrants) and Bouwmaat (the name of a construction company which was the former user of the building). Unusually, the owner did not want to evict the squatters but came to an arrangement with them whereby they could stay for a fixed time as long as the building costs were paid. The security of short term tenure allowed the former squatters to break the offices up into residential units and spaces which small businesses could rent affordably, thus supplying enough money to pay the costs of electricity, water, insurance and so on. A foundation (Stichting Noodzaak) was set up to deal with the owner. The initial contract was for six months and has since been extended in six month blocks.<ref name=\"Disegno\">{{cite web |last1=Kafka |first1=George |title=The Vluchtmaat |url=https://www.disegnodaily.com/article/the-vluchtmaat |website=Disegno |accessdate=14 May 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514142027/https://www.disegnodaily.com/article/the-vluchtmaat|archivedate=14 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nAnother subgroup of We Are Here is composed of [[Swahili language]] speakers. They first squatted on Amstelstraat in the centre of Amsterdam at the end of 2016.<ref name=\"Vastgoedmarkt\">{{cite news |title=Uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers kraken A-locatie |url=https://www.vastgoedmarkt.nl/regios/nieuws/2017/01/uitgeprocedeerde-asielzoekers-kraken-a-locatie-101118483?vakmedianet-approve-cookies=1 |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Vastgoedmarkt |date=4 January 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712074710/https://www.vastgoedmarkt.nl/regios/nieuws/2017/01/uitgeprocedeerde-asielzoekers-kraken-a-locatie-101118483?vakmedianet-approve-cookies=1 |archivedate=12 July 2019 |language=NL}}</ref> They then occupied a disused kindergarten in [[Amsterdam-Zuidoost]] in May 2017 and a building on [[Sarphatistraat]] in September of the same year.<ref name=\"Haardstee\">{{cite news |title=Vluchtelingen Wij Zijn Hier kraken Haardstee |url=https://www.zuidoost.tv/zuidoost/vluchtelingen-wij-zijn-hier-kraken-haardstee/ |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Zuidoost TV |date=30 May 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705212336/https://www.zuidoost.tv/zuidoost/vluchtelingen-wij-zijn-hier-kraken-haardstee/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Sarphatistraat\">{{cite news |title='Wij zijn hier' kraakt pand aan Sarphatistraat |url=https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/172688/wij-zijn-hier-kraakt-pand-aan-sarphatistraat |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=AT5 |date=4 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712082752/https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/172688/wij-zijn-hier-kraakt-pand-aan-sarphatistraat |archive-date=12 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> In May 2018, they were occupying the former discotheque Club Empire on Buikslootermeerplein in [[Amsterdam-Noord]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Claus |first1=Ryan |title=We Are Here: 'Dit is mijn land en ik ga niet meer weg!' |url=https://revu.nl/artikel/we-are-here-dit-is-mijn-land-en-ik-ga-niet-meer-weg |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Revu |date=24 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709210353/https://revu.nl/artikel/we-are-here-dit-is-mijn-land-en-ik-ga-niet-meer-weg |archivedate=9 July 2019 |language=NL |quote=Meer}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, the We Are Here subgroup composed of men from [[West Africa]], [[Ethiopia]], [[Eritrea]] and [[Sudan]] occupied a derelict office building on Nienoord street in [[Diemen]]. The owner was the Arq Group, which specialises in treating people with severe psychotraumas which cannot be treated by psychologists or psychiatrists.<ref name=\"Wolthuizen2\">{{cite news |last1=Wolthuizen |first1=Josien |title=Arrestatie bij ontruiming 29ste onderkomen Wij Zijn Hier |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~b276a1a0/ |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Parool |date=17 November 2017 |language=NL |quote=Over twee jaar wordt het gesloopt, maar vanwege de asbest kunnen we het niet verhuren. Daarom vinden we ook dat er geen mensen zouden moeten wonen. Het is hartstikke gevaarlijk|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703201501/https://www.ad.nl/amsterdam/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~a276a1a0/|archivedate=3 July 2019}}</ref> The owner was sympathetic to the squatters but said the building contained asbestos and therefore was unliveable.<ref name=\"Wolthuizen2\"/> We Are Here denounced Arq for not making a temporary contract since the building would not be demolished for two years and added that many in the group had actually attended treatment sessions for trauma provided by the group's Equator Foundation.<ref name=\"Geschiedenis2\">{{cite web |title=Geschiedenis van Wij Zijn Hier |url=http://wijzijnhier.org/tijdslijn/geschiedenis-van-wij-zijn-hier/ |website=Wij Zijn Hier |accessdate=10 July 2019 |language=EN |quote=See note 33 on map: The men from west Africa, Ethiopia, eritrea and Sudan had to leave #31. They moved to an abandoned office building in the same area. It belongs to the Arq Psychotrauma Expert Groep. WE ARE HERE is no stranger to Arq. Many people of WE ARE HERE visited in the past the Equator institution, part of the Arq group, to deal with trauma healing. Arq opposed to the squat and didn't want to give a temporary contract to the refugees  to stay in their vacant office. On 17 november the building was evicted by the police even though Arq will let this building stay empty for at least 2 years. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705212427/https://wijzijnhier.org/tijdslijn/geschiedenis-van-wij-zijn-hier/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Normally the group would leave a building willingly after a court order or having made an agreement with the owner, but in this case the squatters said they would resist the eviction, since they were tired of constantly moving.<ref name=\"Kapot\">{{cite news |title=Wij Zijn Hier-leden kondigen verzet aan bij ontruiming |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/wij-zijn-hier-leden-kondigen-verzet-aan-bij-ontruiming~bd8c4a9c/ |accessdate=10 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=16 November 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620222047/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/wij-zijn-hier-leden-kondigen-verzet-aan-bij-ontruiming~bd8c4a9c/ |archivedate=20 June 2019 |language=NL |quote='Wij zijn kapot van het rondzwerven en hebben besloten niet vrijwillig te vertrekken. We hebben al onze sympathisanten opgeroepen ons te komen ondersteunen in ons vreedzaam verzet.'}}</ref> The building was evicted in November 2017 by the police, with one arrest. It was the 29th building which had been squatted by We Are Here since 2012.<ref name=\"Wolthuizen3\">{{cite news |last1=Wolthuizen |first1=Josien |title=Arrestatie bij ontruiming 29ste onderkomen Wij Zijn Hier |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~b276a1a0/ |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Parool |date=17 November 2017 |language=NL |quote=Het was het 29ste pand dat sinds 2012 werd gekraakt door Wij Zijn Hier|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703201501/https://www.ad.nl/amsterdam/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~a276a1a0/|archivedate=3 July 2019}}</ref> Out of the 90 people evicted, 17 were from Sudan. Some said they had escaped the [[Darfur genocide]], but the immigration authorities had refused their claims.<ref name=\"Dabanga\">{{cite news |title=Darfur refugees among 90 forcibly evicted in Amsterdam |url=https://www.dabangasudan.org/en/all-news/article/darfur-refugees-among-90-forcibly-evicted-in-amsterdam |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Radio Dabanga |date=18 November 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171214094235/https://www.dabangasudan.org/en/all-news/article/darfur-refugees-among-90-forcibly-evicted-in-amsterdam |archivedate=14 December 2017 |language=EN |quote=A human rights activist told Radio Dabanga that the Dutch immigration authority has closed the files of 17 Sudanese nationals in the Netherlands including Darfuris, as they do not believe they come from Darfur. The refugees said they had proved it, but the immigration authorities doubted their arguments.}}</ref>\n\n=== Rudolf Dieselstraat ===\nIn April 2018, We Are Here occupied eleven apartments and a shop on Rudolf Dieselstraat in [[Amsterdam-Oost]]. They renamed the street 'We Are Here Village.' Since the housing corporation, Ymere, had left the apartments empty for some time, they asked that they could stay there until they were demolished and the city council backed their request.<ref name=\"12squats\">{{cite news |title=Amsterdam: asylum seekers squat 12 buildings |url=https://freedomnews.org.uk/amsterdam-asylum-seekers-squat-12-buildings/ |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Freedom |date=4 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514191538/https://freedomnews.org.uk/amsterdam-asylum-seekers-squat-12-buildings/ |archive-date=14 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The previously unknown street became both a media and political sensation with many actors becoming involved in the debate about whether We Are Here should be able to stay or not.<ref name=\"Hiemstra\">{{cite news |last1=Hiemstra |first1=Eelco |title=Straks compact wonen in de nieuwe 'Rudolf Dieselbuurt' |url=https://oost-online.nl/straks-compact-wonen-in-de-nieuwe-rudolf-dieselbuurt/ |language=NL|accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Oost Online |date=26 January 2019|quote=Ongedocumenteerde vluchtelingen van We Are Here kraakten er tijdens de paasdagen een aantal woningen en vanaf dat moment wisten vele voor- en tegenstanders, journalisten en politici de tot dan toe relatief onbekende straat te vinden.}}</ref><ref name=\"12Panden\">{{cite news |title=Uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers kraken 12 panden in Oost |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/uitgeprocedeerde-asielzoekers-kraken-12-panden-in-oost~b55865e3/ |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=Parool |language=NL |date=3 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703154548/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/uitgeprocedeerde-asielzoekers-kraken-12-panden-in-oost~b55865e3/ |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"NLTimesEviction\">{{cite news |last1=Pieters |first1=Janine |title=Business Amsterdam squatters turn to court over eviction |url=https://nltimes.nl/2018/04/13/amsterdam-squatters-turn-court-eviction |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=NL Times |language=EN}}</ref><ref name=\"Soft\">{{cite news |last1=Brown |first1=Emma |title=Is the Netherlands too soft on squatting asylum seekers? |url=https://dutchreview.com/news/dutch/is-the-netherlands-too-soft-on-squatting-asylum-seekers/ |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Dutch Review |date=11 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn Parliament, [[Centre-right politics|centre-right]] parties [[VVD]] and [[Christian Democratic Appeal|CDA]] demanded that the state took action to evict the squatters.<ref name=\"NOS-woningen\">{{cite news |title=De gekraakte woningen in Amsterdam-Oost ANP VVD en CDA willen dat kabinet ingrijpt in Amsterdam om krakende illegalen |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=NOS |agency=ANP |date=18 May 2018 |language=NL |quote=Het kabinet moet in Amsterdam ingrijpen in de zaak van illegalen die corporatiewoningen hebben gekraakt, vinden de regeringspartijen VVD en CDA in de Tweede Kamer. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703145031/https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> This was in response from a motion at the [[Government of Amsterdam|Amsterdam city council]] put forward by [[Centre-left politics|centre-left]] parties [[Democrats 66|D66]], [[Labour Party (Netherlands)|PvdA]], [[Socialist Party (Netherlands)|SP]] and [[GroenLinks]] proposing that the council would not put asylum seekers on the street and would ask owners of occupied buildings not to evict migrants.<ref name=\"NOS-woningen2\">{{cite news |title=De gekraakte woningen in Amsterdam-Oost ANP VVD en CDA willen dat kabinet ingrijpt in Amsterdam om krakende illegalen |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=NOS |agency=ANP |date=18 May 2018 |language=NL |quote=Met steun van D66, PvdA en SP kreeg GroenLinks een motie door de raad waarin staat dat de gemeente voorlopig geen uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers op straat zet en pandeigenaren verzoekt geen ontruiming aan te vragen. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703145031/https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Acting mayor [[Jozias van Aartsen]] (from VVD party) was against the motion. He later received criticism from within his party for not taking further action and replied that \"You must be very careful with the mayor's office and not go down the route of politicize the mayor's role.\"<ref name=\"AT5-trekken\">{{cite news |title=Van Aartsen: 'Ik heb geen enkele zin om me in debat over krakers te laten trekken' |url=https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/180774/van-aartsen-ik-heb-geen-enkele-zin-om-me-in-debat-over-krakers-te-laten-trekken |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=AT5 |date=13 April 2018 |language=NL |quote=U moet heel voorzichtig zijn met het ambt burgemeester en niet de route op gaan om de burgemeester te politiseren. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703152756/https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/180774/van-aartsen-ik-heb-geen-enkele-zin-om-me-in-debat-over-krakers-te-laten-trekken |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> CDA Parliament member [[Madeleine van Toorenburg]] stated that \"the enforcement of the [2010 [[Dutch squatting ban|criminalisation of squatting]]] law is a joke.\"<ref name=\"NOS-woningen3\">{{cite news |title=De gekraakte woningen in Amsterdam-Oost ANP VVD en CDA willen dat kabinet ingrijpt in Amsterdam om krakende illegalen |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=NOS |agency=ANP |date=18 May 2018 |language=NL |quote=Volgens Van Toorenburg wordt de wet niet goed gehandhaafd en worden krakers in de praktijk niet vervolgd na een aangifte. \"De handhaving van de wet is een lachertje\", zei ze in het debat. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703145031/https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe housing corporation, Ymere, went to court to evict the squatters. The judge decided that Ymere was not demonstrating an immediate need for the buildings, which would eventually be demolished. He stated that the squat action had not disturbed the public order and that the squatters could stay until 1 June.<ref name=\"NOS-woningen4\">{{cite news |title=De gekraakte woningen in Amsterdam-Oost ANP VVD en CDA willen dat kabinet ingrijpt in Amsterdam om krakende illegalen |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=NOS |agency=ANP |date=18 May 2018 |language=NL |quote=Woningcorporatie Ymere heeft volgens hem niet hard kunnen maken dat onmiddellijke ontruiming nodig is omdat anders de nieuwbouw van 144 woningen vertraging oploopt. Ook was de rechter niet overtuigd dat de openbare orde ernstig verstoord was door de kraakactie. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703145031/https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The situation then worsened when a far-right group announced they would also occupy a building on the same estate in protest at the migrant action. Identitair Verzet (a small Dutch branch of [[Generation Identity]]) claimed they had squatted a building but Ymere later stated a [[property guardian]] had let them into a house.<ref name=\"AT5-sleutel\">{{cite news |title=We Are Here vermoedt complot: 'Rechtse krakers kregen sleutel' |url=https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/181127/we-are-here-vermoedt-complot-rechtse-krakers-kregen-sleutel |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=AT5 |date=21 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703152804/https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/181127/we-are-here-vermoedt-complot-rechtse-krakers-kregen-sleutel |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The house was immediately attacked with fireworks and had its windows smashed.<ref name=\"AT5-vuurwerk\">{{cite news |title=Confrontatie met actievoerders Rudolf Dieselstraat: ramen ingegooid en vuurwerk afgestoken |url=https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/181140/ramen-ingegooid-van-woning-met-actievoerders-in-rudolf-dieselstraat |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=AT5 |date=21 April 2018 |language=NL |quote=Op beelden is het ingooien van de ruiten te horen. Ook is te zien dat er vuurwerk is afgestoken. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703153344/https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/181140/ramen-ingegooid-van-woning-met-actievoerders-in-rudolf-dieselstraat |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The police then evicted the house on grounds of public order. Identitair Verzet had also previously tried to demonstrate against the Vluchtkerk.<ref name=\"afgeblazen\">{{cite news |title=ID Verzet is 'rechtse splintergroepering' |url=https://www.nu.nl/binnenland/3503679/id-verzet-rechtse-splintergroepering.html |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Nu |agency=ANP |date=18 June 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150624183557/http://www.nu.nl/binnenland/3503679/id-verzet-rechtse-splintergroepering.html |archivedate=24 June 2015 |language=NL |quote=De Vluchtkerk in Amsterdam kreeg in april met ID Verzet te maken. Een aangekondigde demonstratie bij de Vluchtkerk ging niet door. Burgemeester Eberhard van der Laan stond protest wel toe, maar dan op een locatie bij de Zuidas. Daarop werd de demonstratie afgeblazen.}}</ref> The houses occupied by the We Are Here collective were subsequently evicted in June.<ref name=\"GDA\">{{cite news |last1=Muller |first1=Mike |title=Getergd door asielkrakers |url=https://www.telegraaf.nl/nieuws/2137142/getergd-door-asielkrakers |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=Telegraaf |date=7 June 2018 |language=nl}}</ref>\n\n=== 2018\u2013 ===\n[[File:20180428PlacardsWeAreHere.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Placards at 2018 demonstration|alt=refer to caption]]\nWe Are Here then squatted a building in [[Amstelveen]] on Groen van Prinstererlaan in early June 2018, having left Rudolf Dieselstraat. They had briefly occupied a former bowling alley in [[Amsterdam-Noord]] and failed to squat at Hoog Kadijk and Weesperzijde.<ref name=\"Pieters\">{{cite news |last1=Pieters |first1=Janene |title=Politics Amsterdam squatters move into Amstelveen building |url=https://nltimes.nl/2018/06/05/amsterdam-squatters-move-amstelveen-building |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=NL Times |date=5 June 2018}}</ref> They were then given an eviction order for the end of the month.<ref name=\"Amstelveen\">{{cite news |title=We Are Here group ordered to leave office block in Amstelveen |url=https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2018/06/we-are-here-group-ordered-to-leave-office-block-in-amstelveen/ |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Dutch News |date=25 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514191536/https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2018/06/we-are-here-group-ordered-to-leave-office-block-in-amstelveen/ |archive-date=14 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe Weesperzijde squat action at a former [[United Nations]] building became a notorious incident, since the building was actually inhabited. A heated confrontation between We Are Here and a resident, who happened to be the son of the chair of the local branch of the [[VVD]] (the party of Prime Minister [[Mark Rutte]]), was filmed and circulated in the press.<ref name=\"Heftige\">{{cite news |title=Zien: heftige confrontatie krakers en bewoner |url=https://www.telegraaf.nl/video/2121500/zien-heftige-confrontatie-krakers-en-bewoner |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Telegraaf |date=4 June 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413071715/https://www.telegraaf.nl/video/2121500/zien-heftige-confrontatie-krakers-en-bewoner |archivedate=13 April 2019 |language=NL}}</ref><ref name=\"Break\">{{cite news |last1=Brown |first1=Emma |title=\u2018We Are Here\u2019 squatters stopped by residents when they try and break in (vid inside!) |url=https://dutchreview.com/news/dutch/we-are-here-squatters-stopped-by-residents-when-they-try-and-break-in-vid-inside/ |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Dutch Review |date=5 June 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711171614/https://dutchreview.com/news/dutch/we-are-here-squatters-stopped-by-residents-when-they-try-and-break-in-vid-inside/ |archivedate=11 July 2019}}</ref> In April 2019, member of the collective Fortune M. was given a three-day jail sentence and a conditional fine of \u20ac150, for damaging a door during the attempt to squat the building.<ref name=\"Boete\">{{cite news |title=Celstraf en voorwaardelijke boete lid We Are Here |url=https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/celstraf-en-voorwaardelijke-boete-lid-we-are-here~b5a819f3/ |accessdate=10 May 2019 |work=Parool |agency=ANP |date=26 April 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510193818/https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/celstraf-en-voorwaardelijke-boete-lid-we-are-here~b5a819f3/ |archivedate=10 May 2019 |quote=De politierechter in Amsterdam heeft de 36-jarige Fortune M., lid van het vluchtelingencollectief We Are Here, veroordeeld tot een celstraf van drie dagen en een voorwaardelijke geldboete van 150 euro.}}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\n* 2014: Photographer Manel Quiros won third place in the [[International Photography Awards]] with a photoseries following We Are Here.<ref name=\"IPA\">{{cite web |title=We Are Here |url=https://photoawards.com/winner/zoom.php?eid=8-135031-17 |website=International Photography Awards |accessdate=5 July 2019 |language=EN}}</ref>\n* 2015-2016: Inspired by meeting members of the We Are Here collective and following them around for several months, Dutch artist Manon van Hoeckel created the Limbo Embassy. This provided a way for people to hear the stories of We Are Here participants. It was also a means for them to earn money, important since they were otherwise not allowed to work or volunteer, but because it was an artistic project they could be paid for performances and sell political printed matter. Between June 2015 to June 2016, the embassy visited 15 events, including the [[Dutch Design Week]] in [[Eindhoven]].<ref name=\"Limbo\" /><ref name=\"Locals\">{{cite news |last1=Reimerink |first1=Letty |title=In Amsterdam, an 'Embassy' Where Migrants Connect With Locals |url=https://www.citylab.com/design/2015/09/in-amsterdam-an-embassy-where-migrants-connect-with-locals/406102/ |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=City Lab |date=18 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711211530/https://www.citylab.com/design/2015/09/in-amsterdam-an-embassy-where-migrants-connect-with-locals/406102/ |archive-date=11 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* 2015: Alexandra Jansse made an hour long documentary called ''Wij Zijn Hier'' about the group <ref name=\"Hacks\">{{cite web |title=Hacks/Hackers Amsterdam is organizing a 'Refugee Hackathon' from February 4\u20136 at A-Lab. |url=http://hackshackers.nl/media/ |website=Hacks Hackers |accessdate=3 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830180058/http://hackshackers.nl/media/ |archive-date=30 August 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* 2017: We Are Here featured in the exhibition ''Architecture of Appropriation'' at [[Netherlands Architecture Institute|Het Nieuwe Instituut]] (the Dutch Institute of Architecture), in [[Rotterdam]].<ref name=\"RIBAJ\">{{cite web |last1=Buxton |first1=Pamela |title=Squatting as urban regeneration |url=https://www.ribaj.com/culture/architecture-of-appropriation |website=RIBAJ |accessdate=25 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525072658/https://www.ribaj.com/culture/architecture-of-appropriation |archive-date=25 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* 2018: Artist Hilda Moucharrafieh won the International Bursary Award at the Amsterdam Fringe Festival for her project ''Tracing Erased Memories: A parallel walk of Amsterdam & Cairo.'' She worked with members of We Are Here to make a choreographed roadmap in which a person walked through central Amsterdam wearing headphones and hearing the sounds of someone walking through central Cairo.<ref name=\"HKU\">{{cite news |title=Hilda Moucharrafieh wins the International Bursary Award |url=https://www.hku.nl/Home/Education/Masters/MAProgrammeScenography/NewsAndEvents/NewsAndEvents/HildaMoucharrafiehWinsTheInternationalBursaryAward.htm |accessdate=14 May 2019 |work=HKU |date=24 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514142026/https://www.hku.nl/Home/Education/Masters/MAProgrammeScenography/NewsAndEvents/NewsAndEvents/HildaMoucharrafiehWinsTheInternationalBursaryAward.htm |archive-date=14 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* 2018: Academics who have studied We Are Here organised a meeting at Spui 25 cultural centre to discuss their findings with members of the collective and to listen to their feedback.<ref name=\"Idzikowska\">{{cite web |last1=Idzikowska |first1=Ula |title=Wat leert de wetenschap ons over We Are Here? |url=https://www.oneworld.nl/movement/welke-lessen-leert-de-wetenschap-ons-over-we-are-here/ |website=One World |accessdate=5 July 2019 |date=2018-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703154441/https://www.oneworld.nl/movement/welke-lessen-leert-de-wetenschap-ons-over-we-are-here/ |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Abahlali baseMjondolo]]\n*[[Calais Jungle]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Spijkerboer, Thomas (2013) ''\u201cWij zijn hier\u201d. Gelijke behandeling van niet uitzetbare vreemdelingen?'' [http://dare.ubvu.vu.nl/bitstream/handle/1871/40177/Artikel?sequence=1 Artikel 1 lezing] (pdf in Dutch)\n*Slingenberg, Lieneke & Bonneau, Louise (2017) [https://brill.com/view/journals/emil/19/4/article-p335_335.xml?lang=en (In)formal Migrant Settlements and Right to Respect for a Home] in ''European Journal of Migration and Law'' Vol 19:4 pp335\u2013369 10.1163/15718166-12340013\n*Truijen, K. (2019) ''Architecture of Appropriation - On Squatting as Spatial Practice'' {{ISBN|9789083015200}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://wijzijnhier.org Official website]\n* [http://wijzijnhier.org/tijdslijn/geschiedenis-van-wij-zijn-hier/ Timeline of events up to mid 2015]\n\n{{Squatting}}\n{{SquatNL}}\n\n[[Category:Squatters' movements]]\n[[Category:Squatting in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:European migrant crisis]]\n[[Category:Amsterdam]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in the Netherlands]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Human rights campaign of migrants in Amsterdam}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name                = We Are Here\n| native_name         = Wij Zijn Hier\n| native_name_lang    = NL\n| image               = File:20180428BannerWeAreHere.jpg\n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = Banner at 2018 demonstration\n| caption             = Banner at 2018 demonstration\n| map                 = File:Amsterdamse stadsdelen 2010.png\n| map_size            = \n| map_alt             = Boroughs of Amsterdam\n| map_caption         = Boroughs of Amsterdam\n| logo                = \n| logo_size           = \n| logo_alt            = \n| logo_caption        = \n| abbreviation        = WZH\n| nickname            = \n| formation           = {{start date and age|2012|09|04}}\n| founding_location   = Garden of Diakonie, Amsterdam\n| location            = Amsterdam\n| purpose             = Rights for migrants\n| methods             = Campaigning, Demonstrations, Direct Action, Squatting\n| website             = {{URL|wijzijnhier.org}}\n}}\n'''We Are Here''' ([[Dutch (language)|Dutch]]: '''Wij Zijn Hier''') is a [[collective]] of migrants based in [[Amsterdam]], the [[Netherlands]], which campaigns for human rights for its members and all undocumented migrants. The asylum seekers have in many cases had their applications to remain in the Netherlands denied but they either cannot go back or refuse to return to their country of origin. They ask for access to social services such as medical care and housing.\n\nThe group is constantly in flux as a result of individually precarious legal situations. Since its members refuse to use the [[homeless shelter]]s offered by the city of Amsterdam, which can only be used from 5 pm until 9 am, the collective has [[Squatting|squatted]] a chain of buildings in and around the city since 2012. Most buildings are quickly evicted, some have led to offshoot projects. The group is mostly composed of men originally from Africa, although there have also been women only occupations. There have been some successes, such as the Vluchtmaat, where a longterm deal was negotiated with the owner, and some longterm squats such as the Vluchtgarage, where [[Amsterdam city council]] tolerated the occupation. As of 2017, roughly one hundred people from the group had gained Dutch residence permits.\n\nBy 2018, the new council had pledged to set up 24 hour shelters for up to 500 undocumented migrants, but We Are Here stated it was against the shelters since they were only for a short time period and it disputed the plan to send asylum seekers back to their country of origin at the end of the project. The collective by this point had diversified into different subgroups occupying different buildings, such as a women-only group, a [[Swahili language]] group, and a group composed of people mainly from [[Ethiopia]], [[Eritrea]] and [[Sudan]].\n\n== Background ==\nRefugees seeking asylum in the Netherlands are assessed by the [[Immigration and Naturalisation Service (Netherlands)|Immigration and Naturalisation Service]] and then either gain residency or fail to do so, based on their documentary evidence. For some who have fled warzones, it is difficult to provide documents or other proof for their claim. If the refugees fail to be granted asylum, they are given temporary housing and have 28 days to leave. Some people fall into \"the asylum gap\" since they are unable to return to their country of origin, whilst others want to go back but cannot because they do not possess the required visas or identity documents. In 2016, it was estimated there were 35,000 undocumented migrants in the Netherlands. Without a residence permit they are denied access to social services such as healthcare and housing.<ref name=\"Limbo\">{{cite news |last1=Merks |first1=Kelly |title=Life in Limbo in the Netherlands |url=https://access-nl.org/features/life-in-limbo-in-nl/ |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Access Magazine |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711164915/https://access-nl.org/features/life-in-limbo-in-nl/ |archivedate=11 July 2019 |language=EN}}</ref><ref name=\"Brechtje\">{{cite news |last1=Keulen |first1=Brechtje |title=\u2018Wij zijn allemaal moe\u2019 |url=https://www.groene.nl/artikel/wij-zijn-allemaal-moe|accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Groene Amsterdammer |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712153050/https://www.groene.nl/artikel/wij-zijn-allemaal-moe |archivedate=12 July 2019 |language=NL}}</ref>\n\nThe migrants of the We Are Here [[collective]] had by the end of 2017 occupied over 30 buildings and parks.<ref name=\"Koops\">{{cite news |last1=Wolthuizen |first1=Josien |last2=Koops |first2=Ruben |title=We Are Here: Vijf jaar later nog geen stap verder |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-vijf-jaar-later-nog-geen-stap-verder~bdbdf167/ |accessdate=10 May 2019 |work=Parool |date=1 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510200206/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-vijf-jaar-later-nog-geen-stap-verder~bdbdf167/ |archive-date=10 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> They argue that they should have access to basic needs such as housing and healthcare. The city council of Amsterdam refuses to accede to their demands. Much of the dispute with the Council is that it only offers the so-called BBB service - Bed-Bath-Bread ([[Dutch (language)|Dutch]]: bed-bad-broodvoorziening), that is to say an overnight accommodation open from 5pm until 9am, which cannot be stayed in during the day. The migrants reject this offer as insufficient and say it is in any case often over-subscribed.<ref name=\"Koops\" /> The city council in turn says that its hands are tied by the policy of the [[Dutch Government]].<ref name=\"Karman-1\">{{cite news |last1=Karman |first1=Jasper |title=Havenstraat biedt iedereen hoop |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/havenstraat-biedt-iedereen-hoop~bbfc9f3d/ |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=6 December 2013 |language=NL |quote=Dat tot frustratie van de burgemeester en de gemeenteraad, die allebei graag meer wilden doen, maar moesten blijven herhalen dat niet Amsterdam, maar Den Haag over het asielbeleid gaat en dat de stad geen asielzoekers m\u00e1g opvangen. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705210244/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/havenstraat-biedt-iedereen-hoop~bbfc9f3d/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Therefore, We Are Here have chosen to [[Squatting|squat]] a number of buildings to live in. By 2019, the total had risen to over 50 squats according to the group's own count. The occupations are tracked on a map hosted on the We Are Here website.<ref name=\"Geschiedenis1\">{{cite web |title=Geschiedenis van Wij Zijn Hier |url=http://wijzijnhier.org/tijdslijn/geschiedenis-van-wij-zijn-hier/ |website=We Are Here |accessdate=12 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705212427/https://wijzijnhier.org/tijdslijn/geschiedenis-van-wij-zijn-hier/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nWe Are Here is mostly composed of men originally from Africa. In some occupations, it was men only, for example the Vluchgarage.<ref name=\"BBB-meer-2\">{{cite web |title=BED, BAD, BROOD EN M\u00c9\u00c9R\u2026 |url=https://vluchtverhalen.nl/we-are-here-wij-zijn-hier/ |website=Vluchtverhalen |accessdate=5 July 2019 |language=NL |quote=Het zijn alleen mannen, afkomstig uit vooral Afrikaanse en Arabische landen. |date=2017-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705210220/https://vluchtverhalen.nl/we-are-here-wij-zijn-hier/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, there have also been women only squats.<ref name=\"Stopera\">{{cite news |title=We Are Here-vrouwen demonstreren bij Stopera |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-vrouwen-demonstreren-bij-stopera~b1418ee91/ |accessdate=9 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=10 April 2018 |language=NL |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709215458/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-vrouwen-demonstreren-bij-stopera~b1418ee91/ |archive-date=9 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The group's membership changes often since people are often being deported or detained. Overall, representatives of the group estimated that over one hundred people had gained residence permits.<ref name=\"Koops\" /> For example, a spokesperson for the group, Khalid Jone, who escaped war in Sudan and had lived in the Netherlands for 16 years, was granted a residence permit in 2018.<ref name=\"Kieft\">{{cite news |last1=Kieft |first1=Tom |title=We Are Here-woordvoerder krijgt na 16 jaar verblijfsvergunning |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-woordvoerder-krijgt-na-16-jaar-verblijfsvergunning~b7a7df8c/ |quote=Toen hij dinsdag zijn email opende en las dat hem een verblijfsvergunning zou zijn toegekend, geloofde hij het niet. |accessdate=14 May 2019 |work=Parool |date=18 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510201146/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-woordvoerder-krijgt-na-16-jaar-verblijfsvergunning~b7a7df8c/ |archive-date=10 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The collective regularly makes demonstrations highlighting the plight of individuals.<ref name=\"Stopera\" /> It has also set up the We Are Here Academy, a scheme to offer university level qualifications for undocumented migrants.<ref>{{Cite book | url=https://books.google.com/?id=gsRlDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA54&lpg=PA54&dq=%22wij+zijn+hier%22+squatters+amsterdam#v=onepage&q=%22wij%20zijn%20hier%22%20squatters%20amsterdam&f=false |title = Solidarity and the 'Refugee Crisis' in Europe|isbn = 9783319918488|last1 = Agust\u00edn|first1 = \u00d3scar Garc\u00eda|last2 = J\u00f8rgensen|first2 = Martin Bak|date = 2018-07-19}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, a newly elected [[Amsterdam city council]], now controlled by a[[Centre-left politics|centre-left]] coalition of [[GroenLinks]], [[Democrats 66|D66]], [[Labour Party (Netherlands)|PvdA]] and [[Socialist Party (Netherlands)|SP]], decided to go against the will of the [[States General of the Netherlands|Parliament]] and to set up a 24-hour [[Homeless shelter|shelter]] for homeless failed asylum seekers.<ref name=\"probeert\">{{cite news |last1=van Unen |first1=David |title=We Are Here probeert tevergeefs nieuw pand te kraken |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-probeert-tevergeefs-nieuw-pand-te-kraken~bed3bff7/ |accessdate=10 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=3 June 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510193834/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-probeert-tevergeefs-nieuw-pand-te-kraken~bed3bff7/?utm_source=link&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=shared%20content&utm_content=free |archivedate=10 May 2019 |quote=Het nieuwe college van Groenlinks, D66, PvdA en SP wil, ondanks weerstand uit Den Haag, 24-uursopvang gaan aanbieden voor de veelal uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers van We Are Here. De groep is echter niet van plan daar gebruik van te maken, herhaalt Jone zondag nog eens.}}</ref> However, We Are Here as a group announced it would not make use of the shelter, since it would only exist for a maximum time of eighteen months and (as part of the proposal) afterwards migrants would have to return to their country of origin. Since We Are Here was set up for people unable to return to their motherland, a spokesman said the plan offered no real solution.<ref name=\"probeert2\">{{cite news |last1=van Unen |first1=David |title=We Are Here probeert tevergeefs nieuw pand te kraken |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-probeert-tevergeefs-nieuw-pand-te-kraken~bed3bff7/ |accessdate=10 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=3 June 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510193834/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/we-are-here-probeert-tevergeefs-nieuw-pand-te-kraken~bed3bff7/?utm_source=link&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=shared%20content&utm_content=free |archivedate=10 May 2019 |quote=De nieuwe opvang biedt voor maximaal anderhalf jaar een oplossing. Daarna moeten asielzoekers meewerken aan een terugkeer naar het land van herkomst, terwijl dat juist niet is wat We Are Here wil. Jone vreest dat hij en leden van z'n groep dan na zes maanden terug de straat op moeten of vastgezet worden.}}</ref> In March 2019, the council announced seven prospective sites for its plan to set up shelters for undocumented migrants. It was considering up to 23 sites, with around 30 beds at each. The cities of Rotterdam, Utrecht, Groningen and Eindhoven stated that they were all also looking for sites.<ref name=\"opvang\">{{cite news |last1=Raap |first1=Rebekka |last2=Hielkema |first2=David |title=Dit zijn de 7 mogelijke locaties voor opvang van asielzoekers |url=https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/dit-zijn-de-7-mogelijke-locaties-voor-opvang-van-asielzoekers~b5e9e7d2/ |accessdate=10 July 2019 |date=12 March 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510193847/https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/dit-zijn-de-7-mogelijke-locaties-voor-opvang-van-asielzoekers~b5e9e7d2/ |archivedate=10 May 2019 |language=NL}}</ref>\n\n[[Femke Halsema]] (previously [[parliamentary leader]] of [[GroenLinks]]) started serving a six-year term as [[Mayor of Amsterdam]] in July 2018. In 2019 she discussed making the enforcement of the [[Dutch squatting ban]] tougher and suggested that the immigration police could be employed to stop the We Are Here collective squatting. GroenLinks asked for clarification since the tradition in Amsterdam is that illegal migrants are not searched for by the police.<ref name=\"Koops-Halsema\">{{cite news |last1=Koops |first1=Ruben |title=Halsema: \u2018Illegalen die geen strafbare feiten plegen hebben niets te vrezen\u2019 |url=https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/halsema-illegalen-die-geen-strafbare-feiten-plegen-hebben-niets-te-vrezen~b4613d26/ |accessdate=27 December 2019 |work=Het Parool |date=18 December 2019 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/CHKjh |archivedate=14 March 2020 |language=nl-NL |quote=GroenLinks had om opheldering gevraagd, nadat Halsema eerder dit jaar zei dat zij de vreemdelingenpolitie wil inschakelen tegen de asielactivisten van We Are Here [...] GroenLinks was bang dat de burgemeester daarmee afscheid nam van de Amsterdamse traditie dat op illegale vreemdelingen in principe niet gejaagd wordt door de veiligheidsdiensten. |url-status=live }}</ref> Halsema stated that if We Are Here members did nothing wrong they had nothing to fear, but that squatting was a criminal offence. GroenLinks stated it was troubled by this position.<ref name=\"Koops-Halsema2\">{{cite news |last1=Koops |first1=Ruben |title=Halsema: \u2018Illegalen die geen strafbare feiten plegen hebben niets te vrezen\u2019 |url=https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/halsema-illegalen-die-geen-strafbare-feiten-plegen-hebben-niets-te-vrezen~b4613d26/ |accessdate=27 December 2019 |work=Het Parool |date=18 December 2019 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/CHKjh |archivedate=14 March 2020 |language=nl-NL |quote=Maar Halsema wees erop dat We Are Here regelmatig de wet breekt, onder meer door bewoonde panden te kraken. \u201cIllegalen die niets hebben gedaan worden niet in detentie geplaatst,\u201d beloofde Halsema. \u201cMaar ook voor We Are Here geldt dat, als er strafbare feiten worden gepleegd, er aanhoudingen volgen en de juridische procedure moet worden doorlopen. Vreemdelingendetentie kan dan de consequentie zijn,\u201d zei Halsema. [...] Onder de achterban van GroenLinks was grote onrust ontstaan om de uitspraken van de burgemeester, zei raadslid Femke Roosma. |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n== Significant occupations ==\n=== 2012\u20132017 ===\nWe Are Here coalesced as a group in 2012, when a small number of asylum seekers whose claims had been rejected decided to make a protest camp at the garden of the Diakonie on the [[Nieuwe Herengracht]] in the [[Grachtengordel]] in central Amsterdam.<ref name=\"29ste-1\">{{cite news |last1=Wolthuizen |first1=Josien |title=Arrestatie bij ontruiming 29ste onderkomen Wij Zijn Hier |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~b276a1a0/ |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Parool |date=17 November 2017 |language=NL |quote=In september van dat jaar sloegen drie asielzoekers uit Eritrea een tentje op in de achtertuin van de Diakonie op de Nieuwe Herengracht |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620222010/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~b276a1a0/ |archive-date=20 June 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> More migrants joined the protest, which then moved location to Notweg in [[Osdorp]]. The camp swelled to 130 people and received national media attention. The camp was evicted on 30 November. Everyone was arrested and some people were held in foreign detention ([[Dutch (language)|Dutch]]: vreemdelingendetentie).<ref name=\"BBB-meer-1\">{{cite web |title=BED, BAD, BROOD EN M\u00c9\u00c9R\u2026 |url=https://vluchtverhalen.nl/we-are-here-wij-zijn-hier/ |website=VLUCHTVERHALEN |publisher=Vluchtverhalen |accessdate=5 July 2019 |quote=Het aantal bewoners in het tentenkamp in Osdorp groeit tot ongeveer 130. De gemeente Amsterdam weet zich niet goed raad met de situatie. De actievoerders krijgen veel steun vanuit de bevolking en de Protestantse Diaconie, maar worden ook bedreigd vanuit rechts-radicale hoek. Vanuit Den Haag wordt druk uitgeoefend de vreemdelingen te wijzen op hun \u2018vertrekplicht\u2018.  Uiteindelijk geeft burgemeester Eberhard van der Laan op 30 november 2012 de politie opdracht het kamp te ontruimen. Vele mensen worden gearresteerd. Een tiental verdwijnt in vreemdelingendetentie. |date=2017-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705210220/https://vluchtverhalen.nl/we-are-here-wij-zijn-hier/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAfter a few nights staying at the Vondelpark Bunker and [[OT301]], the group squatted an empty church in [[Bos en Lommer]]. This became known as the Vluchtkerk, a portmanteau of the Dutch words for migrant ([[Dutch (language)|Dutch]]: vluchteling) and church ([[Dutch (language)|Dutch]]: kerk). This began the tradition of giving every new location a nickname, by adding 'Vlucht' to the type of place. The Vluchtkerk again generated a lot of media attention in the Netherlands.<ref name=\"Rechten\">{{cite news |last1=Steenhuis |first1=Peter Henk |title=Wie geen nationaliteit heeft, heeft geen rechten |url=https://www.trouw.nl/nieuws/wie-geen-nationaliteit-heeft-heeft-geen-rechten~b3d9ceed/ |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Trouw |date=18 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712093803/https://www.trouw.nl/nieuws/wie-geen-nationaliteit-heeft-heeft-geen-rechten~b3d9ceed/ |archive-date=12 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Bescherming\">{{cite news |last1=van Wijk |first1=Lieke |last2=van Wijnbergen |first2=Lucille |title='Illegaliteit strafbaar? Zo criminaliseer je groep die bescherming nodig heeft' |url=https://www.volkskrant.nl/columns-opinie/illegaliteit-strafbaar-zo-criminaliseer-je-groep-die-bescherming-nodig-heeft~b1e2f38b/ |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Volkskrant |date=13 March 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712093715/https://www.volkskrant.nl/columns-opinie/illegaliteit-strafbaar-zo-criminaliseer-je-groep-die-bescherming-nodig-heeft~b1e2f38b/ |archive-date=12 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Celebrities such as popstar [[Anouk (singer)|Anouk]] made solidarity performances.<ref name=\"Anouk\">{{cite news |last1=Redactie |title=Weblog Vluchtkerk: kerst met Anouk en PVV met een geweer |url=https://www.bndestem.nl/overig/weblog-vluchtkerk-kerst-met-anouk-en-pvv-met-een-geweer~ac86971f/ |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=BN DeStem |date=26 December 2012 |language=NL |quote=Afrikaanse muziek is het natuurlijk niet, maar de titel van een van de nummers die Anouk op kerstavond zong tijdens haar verrassingsoptreden in De Vluchtkerk was wel toepasselijk:'I don't wanna hurt no more' ....... |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703133132/https://www.bndestem.nl/overig/weblog-vluchtkerk-kerst-met-anouk-en-pvv-met-een-geweer~ac86971f/ |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> \n\nThe Vluchtkerk was occupied until 31 May 2013. Mayor of Amsterdam [[Eberhard van der Laan]] then asked the group to leave a building they had squatted on the Weteringschans and the council offered the migrants the possibility to stay in a former prison for 6 months. Many people refused, citing bad prior experiences of prisons, but 75 others took the opportunity and it became known as the Vluchthaven.<ref name=\"Eigenraam-1\">{{cite news |last1=Eigenraam |first1=Anouk |title=Amsterdamse asielzoekers kraken nieuw pand |url=https://www.nrc.nl/nieuws/2013/12/13/amsterdamse-asielzoekers-kraken-nieuw-pand-a1428873 |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=NRC |language=NL |quote=Burgemeester Eberhard van der Laan eiste dat de groep uit dit pand zou vertrekken. Ongeveer 75 anderen accepteerden het bod van de gemeente Amsterdam en kregen zo onderdak in een voormalige gevangenis aan de Havenstraat. Ze mogen daar een halfjaar blijven.}}</ref><ref name=\"Karman-2\">{{cite news |last1=Karman |first1=Jasper |title=Havenstraat biedt iedereen hoop |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/havenstraat-biedt-iedereen-hoop~bbfc9f3d/ |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=6 December 2013 |language=NL |quote=Daarnaast riep ook het gebouw zelf weerstand op: bij de aanblik van de gevangenis hadden velen vervelende associaties. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705210244/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/havenstraat-biedt-iedereen-hoop~bbfc9f3d/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Only migrants who signed up with the Dutch Refugee Council were eligible to stay there. To break down the statistics produced at the end of the social experiment, of the 165 people who stayed in the prison, only three returned to their country of origin (three more planned to), only 12 successfully gained residency, one person died and the largest number (38) was formed by those still gathering documents for their asylum process. In terms of country of origin, the largest numbers of people were from Somalia (48), Eritrea (31) and Ethiopia (28).<ref name=\"NewWay\">{{cite news |last1=Devaney |first1=Beulah Maud |title=The city of Amsterdam has come up with a new way to help its refugee population |url=https://www.citymetric.com/city-amsterdam-has-come-new-way-help-its-refugee-population |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=City Metric |date=12 September 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171210215747/http://www.citymetric.com/city-amsterdam-has-come-new-way-help-its-refugee-population |archivedate=10 December 2017 |language=EN}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 December 2013, a building in Amsterdam Zuid Oost was occupied by a group of 90 migrants and their supporters. It was a derelict parking garage with offices attached, which became known as the Vluchtgarage.<ref name=\"Eigenraam-2\">{{cite news |last1=Eigenraam |first1=Anouk |title=Amsterdamse asielzoekers kraken nieuw pand |url=https://www.nrc.nl/nieuws/2013/12/13/amsterdamse-asielzoekers-kraken-nieuw-pand-a1428873 |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=NRC |language=NL |quote=De uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers die sinds begin december door Amsterdam zwerven, hebben vandaag een nieuw pand gekraakt, zo laten ze in een verklaring weten. Het gaat om de groep van negentig asielzoekers die niet in aanmerking kwam voor opvang in een voormalige gevangenis. }}</ref> It was occupied until April 2015. In August 2014, a Somali man called Nassir Guuleed died at the squat. A few days later, Ibrahim Tour\u00e9 from [[C\u00f4te d'Ivoire]] suffered a brain haemorrhage and broken vertebra when he fell off a stairway. Police and ambulance services refused to enter the building (fearing the presence of asbestos despite the city having found none in an inspection earlier that same the day), so the severely injured man was carried to the ambulance.<ref name=\"Hurt\">{{cite news |last1=Hokstam |first1=Marvin |title=Politics Asylum seeker hurt in Amsterdam squat |url=https://nltimes.nl/2014/08/27/asylum-seeker-hurt-amsterdam-squat |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=Dutch News |date=27 August 2014 |language=EN}}</ref>[[Fred Teeven]], [[Undersecretary]] for [[Ministry of Security and Justice (Netherlands)|Security and Justice]] announced his intention to evict the Vluchtgarage in January 2015. At this point there were around 100 people living there.<ref name=\"Teeven-ontruimd\">{{cite news |title=Vluchtgarage Amsterdam wordt ontruimd |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2013173-vluchtgarage-amsterdam-wordt-ontruimd.html |accessdate=5 July 2019 |work=NOS |date=13 January 2015 |language=NL |quote=De ruim honderd uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers die worden opgevangen in de Vluchtgarage in Amsterdam, moeten het gebouw uit. Staatssecretaris Teeven van Justitie laat weten dat de oude garage in Zuidoost ontruimd zal worden. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705204427/https://nos.nl/artikel/2013173-vluchtgarage-amsterdam-wordt-ontruimd.html |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Following the eviction in April 2015, people camped on land in the [[De Pijp]] neighbourhood but were moved on by the council.<ref name=\"Dismantle\">{{cite news |title=Amsterdam tells refugees to dismantle camp on building land |url=https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2015/04/amsterdam-tells-refugees-to-dismantle-camp-on-building-land/ |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Dutch News |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622024941/https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2015/04/amsterdam-tells-refugees-to-dismantle-camp-on-building-land/ |archivedate=22 June 2019 |language=EN}}</ref>\n\nBy 2015, We Are Here was composed in total of around 225 migrants from about 15 countries. As well as occupying several buildings, they regularly made demonstrations demanding rights. The council's response remained the same, namely that it could only offer a hostel that opened at 5pm and closed at 9am, otherwise it would be contravening the policy laid down by [[States General of the Netherlands|Parliament]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Drummond |first1=Lyn |title=Asylum seekers squat empty buildings while waiting for Netherlands approval |url=https://newint.org/features/web-exclusive/2015/10/30/asylum-seekers-wait-for-netherlands-approval |accessdate=10 July 2019 |work=New Internationalist |date=30 October 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710080427/https://newint.org/features/web-exclusive/2015/10/30/asylum-seekers-wait-for-netherlands-approval |archivedate=10 July 2019 |language=EN |quote=NI}}</ref>\nAt each squat, the collective was helped out by local people who donated things. If something was needed, a request was made on the website or on Facebook. Often things were scavenged from the street.<ref>{{Cite book | url=https://books.google.com/?id=r2FTCwAAQBAJ&pg=PT82&lpg=PT82&dq=ontruiming+%22wij+zijn+hier%22+amsterdam#v=onepage&q=ontruiming%20%22wij%20zijn%20hier%22%20amsterdam&f=false |title = EU@Amsterdam: Een stedelijke raad|isbn = 9789048531448|last1 = Mamadouh|first1 = Virginie|last2 = Wageningen|first2 = Anne van|date = 2016-01-05}}</ref> The Vluchtmaat was occupied in 2015 by 40 migrants mainly from [[Ethiopia]] and [[Eritrea]]. The name came from running together the words, Vluchtelingen (migrants) and Bouwmaat (the name of a construction company which was the former user of the building). Unusually, the owner did not want to evict the squatters but came to an arrangement with them whereby they could stay for a fixed time as long as the building costs were paid. The security of short term tenure allowed the former squatters to break the offices up into residential units and spaces which small businesses could rent affordably, thus supplying enough money to pay the costs of electricity, water, insurance and so on. A foundation (Stichting Noodzaak) was set up to deal with the owner. The initial contract was for six months and has since been extended in six month blocks.<ref name=\"Disegno\">{{cite web |last1=Kafka |first1=George |title=The Vluchtmaat |url=https://www.disegnodaily.com/article/the-vluchtmaat |website=Disegno |accessdate=14 May 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514142027/https://www.disegnodaily.com/article/the-vluchtmaat|archivedate=14 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nAnother subgroup of We Are Here is composed of [[Swahili language]] speakers. They first squatted on Amstelstraat in the centre of Amsterdam at the end of 2016.<ref name=\"Vastgoedmarkt\">{{cite news |title=Uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers kraken A-locatie |url=https://www.vastgoedmarkt.nl/regios/nieuws/2017/01/uitgeprocedeerde-asielzoekers-kraken-a-locatie-101118483?vakmedianet-approve-cookies=1 |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Vastgoedmarkt |date=4 January 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712074710/https://www.vastgoedmarkt.nl/regios/nieuws/2017/01/uitgeprocedeerde-asielzoekers-kraken-a-locatie-101118483?vakmedianet-approve-cookies=1 |archivedate=12 July 2019 |language=NL}}</ref> They then occupied a disused kindergarten in [[Amsterdam-Zuidoost]] in May 2017 and a building on [[Sarphatistraat]] in September of the same year.<ref name=\"Haardstee\">{{cite news |title=Vluchtelingen Wij Zijn Hier kraken Haardstee |url=https://www.zuidoost.tv/zuidoost/vluchtelingen-wij-zijn-hier-kraken-haardstee/ |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Zuidoost TV |date=30 May 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705212336/https://www.zuidoost.tv/zuidoost/vluchtelingen-wij-zijn-hier-kraken-haardstee/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Sarphatistraat\">{{cite news |title='Wij zijn hier' kraakt pand aan Sarphatistraat |url=https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/172688/wij-zijn-hier-kraakt-pand-aan-sarphatistraat |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=AT5 |date=4 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712082752/https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/172688/wij-zijn-hier-kraakt-pand-aan-sarphatistraat |archive-date=12 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> In May 2018, they were occupying the former discotheque Club Empire on Buikslootermeerplein in [[Amsterdam-Noord]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Claus |first1=Ryan |title=We Are Here: 'Dit is mijn land en ik ga niet meer weg!' |url=https://revu.nl/artikel/we-are-here-dit-is-mijn-land-en-ik-ga-niet-meer-weg |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Revu |date=24 September 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709210353/https://revu.nl/artikel/we-are-here-dit-is-mijn-land-en-ik-ga-niet-meer-weg |archivedate=9 July 2019 |language=NL |quote=Meer}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, the We Are Here subgroup composed of men from [[West Africa]], [[Ethiopia]], [[Eritrea]] and [[Sudan]] occupied a derelict office building on Nienoord street in [[Diemen]]. The owner was the Arq Group, which specialises in treating people with severe psychotraumas which cannot be treated by psychologists or psychiatrists.<ref name=\"Wolthuizen2\">{{cite news |last1=Wolthuizen |first1=Josien |title=Arrestatie bij ontruiming 29ste onderkomen Wij Zijn Hier |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~b276a1a0/ |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Parool |date=17 November 2017 |language=NL |quote=Over twee jaar wordt het gesloopt, maar vanwege de asbest kunnen we het niet verhuren. Daarom vinden we ook dat er geen mensen zouden moeten wonen. Het is hartstikke gevaarlijk|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703201501/https://www.ad.nl/amsterdam/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~a276a1a0/|archivedate=3 July 2019}}</ref> The owner was sympathetic to the squatters but said the building contained asbestos and therefore was unliveable.<ref name=\"Wolthuizen2\"/> We Are Here denounced Arq for not making a temporary contract since the building would not be demolished for two years and added that many in the group had actually attended treatment sessions for trauma provided by the group's Equator Foundation.<ref name=\"Geschiedenis2\">{{cite web |title=Geschiedenis van Wij Zijn Hier |url=http://wijzijnhier.org/tijdslijn/geschiedenis-van-wij-zijn-hier/ |website=Wij Zijn Hier |accessdate=10 July 2019 |language=EN |quote=See note 33 on map: The men from west Africa, Ethiopia, eritrea and Sudan had to leave #31. They moved to an abandoned office building in the same area. It belongs to the Arq Psychotrauma Expert Groep. WE ARE HERE is no stranger to Arq. Many people of WE ARE HERE visited in the past the Equator institution, part of the Arq group, to deal with trauma healing. Arq opposed to the squat and didn't want to give a temporary contract to the refugees  to stay in their vacant office. On 17 november the building was evicted by the police even though Arq will let this building stay empty for at least 2 years. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705212427/https://wijzijnhier.org/tijdslijn/geschiedenis-van-wij-zijn-hier/ |archive-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Normally the group would leave a building willingly after a court order or having made an agreement with the owner, but in this case the squatters said they would resist the eviction, since they were tired of constantly moving.<ref name=\"Kapot\">{{cite news |title=Wij Zijn Hier-leden kondigen verzet aan bij ontruiming |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/wij-zijn-hier-leden-kondigen-verzet-aan-bij-ontruiming~bd8c4a9c/ |accessdate=10 July 2019 |work=Parool |date=16 November 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620222047/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/wij-zijn-hier-leden-kondigen-verzet-aan-bij-ontruiming~bd8c4a9c/ |archivedate=20 June 2019 |language=NL |quote='Wij zijn kapot van het rondzwerven en hebben besloten niet vrijwillig te vertrekken. We hebben al onze sympathisanten opgeroepen ons te komen ondersteunen in ons vreedzaam verzet.'}}</ref> The building was evicted in November 2017 by the police, with one arrest. It was the 29th building which had been squatted by We Are Here since 2012.<ref name=\"Wolthuizen3\">{{cite news |last1=Wolthuizen |first1=Josien |title=Arrestatie bij ontruiming 29ste onderkomen Wij Zijn Hier |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~b276a1a0/ |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Parool |date=17 November 2017 |language=NL |quote=Het was het 29ste pand dat sinds 2012 werd gekraakt door Wij Zijn Hier|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703201501/https://www.ad.nl/amsterdam/arrestatie-bij-ontruiming-29ste-onderkomen-wij-zijn-hier~a276a1a0/|archivedate=3 July 2019}}</ref> Out of the 90 people evicted, 17 were from Sudan. Some said they had escaped the [[Darfur genocide]], but the immigration authorities had refused their claims.<ref name=\"Dabanga\">{{cite news |title=Darfur refugees among 90 forcibly evicted in Amsterdam |url=https://www.dabangasudan.org/en/all-news/article/darfur-refugees-among-90-forcibly-evicted-in-amsterdam |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Radio Dabanga |date=18 November 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171214094235/https://www.dabangasudan.org/en/all-news/article/darfur-refugees-among-90-forcibly-evicted-in-amsterdam |archivedate=14 December 2017 |language=EN |quote=A human rights activist told Radio Dabanga that the Dutch immigration authority has closed the files of 17 Sudanese nationals in the Netherlands including Darfuris, as they do not believe they come from Darfur. The refugees said they had proved it, but the immigration authorities doubted their arguments.}}</ref>\n\n=== Rudolf Dieselstraat ===\nIn April 2018, We Are Here occupied eleven apartments and a shop on Rudolf Dieselstraat in [[Amsterdam-Oost]]. They renamed the street 'We Are Here Village.' Since the housing corporation, Ymere, had left the apartments empty for some time, they asked that they could stay there until they were demolished and the city council backed their request.<ref name=\"12squats\">{{cite news |title=Amsterdam: asylum seekers squat 12 buildings |url=https://freedomnews.org.uk/amsterdam-asylum-seekers-squat-12-buildings/ |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Freedom |date=4 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514191538/https://freedomnews.org.uk/amsterdam-asylum-seekers-squat-12-buildings/ |archive-date=14 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The previously unknown street became both a media and political sensation with many actors becoming involved in the debate about whether We Are Here should be able to stay or not.<ref name=\"Hiemstra\">{{cite news |last1=Hiemstra |first1=Eelco |title=Straks compact wonen in de nieuwe 'Rudolf Dieselbuurt' |url=https://oost-online.nl/straks-compact-wonen-in-de-nieuwe-rudolf-dieselbuurt/ |language=NL|accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Oost Online |date=26 January 2019|quote=Ongedocumenteerde vluchtelingen van We Are Here kraakten er tijdens de paasdagen een aantal woningen en vanaf dat moment wisten vele voor- en tegenstanders, journalisten en politici de tot dan toe relatief onbekende straat te vinden.}}</ref><ref name=\"12Panden\">{{cite news |title=Uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers kraken 12 panden in Oost |url=https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/uitgeprocedeerde-asielzoekers-kraken-12-panden-in-oost~b55865e3/ |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=Parool |language=NL |date=3 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703154548/https://www.parool.nl/nieuws/uitgeprocedeerde-asielzoekers-kraken-12-panden-in-oost~b55865e3/ |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"NLTimesEviction\">{{cite news |last1=Pieters |first1=Janine |title=Business Amsterdam squatters turn to court over eviction |url=https://nltimes.nl/2018/04/13/amsterdam-squatters-turn-court-eviction |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=NL Times |language=EN}}</ref><ref name=\"Soft\">{{cite news |last1=Brown |first1=Emma |title=Is the Netherlands too soft on squatting asylum seekers? |url=https://dutchreview.com/news/dutch/is-the-netherlands-too-soft-on-squatting-asylum-seekers/ |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Dutch Review |date=11 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn Parliament, [[Centre-right politics|centre-right]] parties [[VVD]] and [[Christian Democratic Appeal|CDA]] demanded that the state took action to evict the squatters.<ref name=\"NOS-woningen\">{{cite news |title=De gekraakte woningen in Amsterdam-Oost ANP VVD en CDA willen dat kabinet ingrijpt in Amsterdam om krakende illegalen |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=NOS |agency=ANP |date=18 May 2018 |language=NL |quote=Het kabinet moet in Amsterdam ingrijpen in de zaak van illegalen die corporatiewoningen hebben gekraakt, vinden de regeringspartijen VVD en CDA in de Tweede Kamer. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703145031/https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> This was in response from a motion at the [[Government of Amsterdam|Amsterdam city council]] put forward by [[Centre-left politics|centre-left]] parties [[Democrats 66|D66]], [[Labour Party (Netherlands)|PvdA]], [[Socialist Party (Netherlands)|SP]] and [[GroenLinks]] proposing that the council would not put asylum seekers on the street and would ask owners of occupied buildings not to evict migrants.<ref name=\"NOS-woningen2\">{{cite news |title=De gekraakte woningen in Amsterdam-Oost ANP VVD en CDA willen dat kabinet ingrijpt in Amsterdam om krakende illegalen |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=NOS |agency=ANP |date=18 May 2018 |language=NL |quote=Met steun van D66, PvdA en SP kreeg GroenLinks een motie door de raad waarin staat dat de gemeente voorlopig geen uitgeprocedeerde asielzoekers op straat zet en pandeigenaren verzoekt geen ontruiming aan te vragen. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703145031/https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Acting mayor [[Jozias van Aartsen]] (from VVD party) was against the motion. He later received criticism from within his party for not taking further action and replied that \"You must be very careful with the mayor's office and not go down the route of politicize the mayor's role.\"<ref name=\"AT5-trekken\">{{cite news |title=Van Aartsen: 'Ik heb geen enkele zin om me in debat over krakers te laten trekken' |url=https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/180774/van-aartsen-ik-heb-geen-enkele-zin-om-me-in-debat-over-krakers-te-laten-trekken |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=AT5 |date=13 April 2018 |language=NL |quote=U moet heel voorzichtig zijn met het ambt burgemeester en niet de route op gaan om de burgemeester te politiseren. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703152756/https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/180774/van-aartsen-ik-heb-geen-enkele-zin-om-me-in-debat-over-krakers-te-laten-trekken |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> CDA Parliament member [[Madeleine van Toorenburg]] stated that \"the enforcement of the [2010 [[Dutch squatting ban|criminalisation of squatting]]] law is a joke.\"<ref name=\"NOS-woningen3\">{{cite news |title=De gekraakte woningen in Amsterdam-Oost ANP VVD en CDA willen dat kabinet ingrijpt in Amsterdam om krakende illegalen |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=NOS |agency=ANP |date=18 May 2018 |language=NL |quote=Volgens Van Toorenburg wordt de wet niet goed gehandhaafd en worden krakers in de praktijk niet vervolgd na een aangifte. \"De handhaving van de wet is een lachertje\", zei ze in het debat. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703145031/https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe housing corporation, Ymere, went to court to evict the squatters. The judge decided that Ymere was not demonstrating an immediate need for the buildings, which would eventually be demolished. He stated that the squat action had not disturbed the public order and that the squatters could stay until 1 June.<ref name=\"NOS-woningen4\">{{cite news |title=De gekraakte woningen in Amsterdam-Oost ANP VVD en CDA willen dat kabinet ingrijpt in Amsterdam om krakende illegalen |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=NOS |agency=ANP |date=18 May 2018 |language=NL |quote=Woningcorporatie Ymere heeft volgens hem niet hard kunnen maken dat onmiddellijke ontruiming nodig is omdat anders de nieuwbouw van 144 woningen vertraging oploopt. Ook was de rechter niet overtuigd dat de openbare orde ernstig verstoord was door de kraakactie. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703145031/https://nos.nl/artikel/2232377-vvd-en-cda-willen-dat-kabinet-ingrijpt-in-amsterdam-om-krakende-illegalen.html |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The situation then worsened when a far-right group announced they would also occupy a building on the same estate in protest at the migrant action. Identitair Verzet (a small Dutch branch of [[Generation Identity]]) claimed they had squatted a building but Ymere later stated a [[property guardian]] had let them into a house.<ref name=\"AT5-sleutel\">{{cite news |title=We Are Here vermoedt complot: 'Rechtse krakers kregen sleutel' |url=https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/181127/we-are-here-vermoedt-complot-rechtse-krakers-kregen-sleutel |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=AT5 |date=21 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703152804/https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/181127/we-are-here-vermoedt-complot-rechtse-krakers-kregen-sleutel |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The house was immediately attacked with fireworks and had its windows smashed.<ref name=\"AT5-vuurwerk\">{{cite news |title=Confrontatie met actievoerders Rudolf Dieselstraat: ramen ingegooid en vuurwerk afgestoken |url=https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/181140/ramen-ingegooid-van-woning-met-actievoerders-in-rudolf-dieselstraat |accessdate=3 July 2019 |work=AT5 |date=21 April 2018 |language=NL |quote=Op beelden is het ingooien van de ruiten te horen. Ook is te zien dat er vuurwerk is afgestoken. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703153344/https://www.at5.nl/artikelen/181140/ramen-ingegooid-van-woning-met-actievoerders-in-rudolf-dieselstraat |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The police then evicted the house on grounds of public order. Identitair Verzet had also previously tried to demonstrate against the Vluchtkerk.<ref name=\"afgeblazen\">{{cite news |title=ID Verzet is 'rechtse splintergroepering' |url=https://www.nu.nl/binnenland/3503679/id-verzet-rechtse-splintergroepering.html |accessdate=12 July 2019 |work=Nu |agency=ANP |date=18 June 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150624183557/http://www.nu.nl/binnenland/3503679/id-verzet-rechtse-splintergroepering.html |archivedate=24 June 2015 |language=NL |quote=De Vluchtkerk in Amsterdam kreeg in april met ID Verzet te maken. Een aangekondigde demonstratie bij de Vluchtkerk ging niet door. Burgemeester Eberhard van der Laan stond protest wel toe, maar dan op een locatie bij de Zuidas. Daarop werd de demonstratie afgeblazen.}}</ref> The houses occupied by the We Are Here collective were subsequently evicted in June.<ref name=\"GDA\">{{cite news |last1=Muller |first1=Mike |title=Getergd door asielkrakers |url=https://www.telegraaf.nl/nieuws/2137142/getergd-door-asielkrakers |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=Telegraaf |date=7 June 2018 |language=nl}}</ref>\n\n=== 2018\u2013 ===\n[[File:20180428PlacardsWeAreHere.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Placards at 2018 demonstration|alt=refer to caption]]\nWe Are Here then squatted a building in [[Amstelveen]] on Groen van Prinstererlaan in early June 2018, having left Rudolf Dieselstraat. They had briefly occupied a former bowling alley in [[Amsterdam-Noord]] and failed to squat at Hoog Kadijk and Weesperzijde.<ref name=\"Pieters\">{{cite news |last1=Pieters |first1=Janene |title=Politics Amsterdam squatters move into Amstelveen building |url=https://nltimes.nl/2018/06/05/amsterdam-squatters-move-amstelveen-building |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=NL Times |date=5 June 2018}}</ref> They were then given an eviction order for the end of the month.<ref name=\"Amstelveen\">{{cite news |title=We Are Here group ordered to leave office block in Amstelveen |url=https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2018/06/we-are-here-group-ordered-to-leave-office-block-in-amstelveen/ |accessdate=20 June 2019 |work=Dutch News |date=25 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514191536/https://www.dutchnews.nl/news/2018/06/we-are-here-group-ordered-to-leave-office-block-in-amstelveen/ |archive-date=14 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe Weesperzijde squat action at a former [[United Nations]] building became a notorious incident, since the building was actually inhabited. A heated confrontation between We Are Here and a resident, who happened to be the son of the chair of the local branch of the [[VVD]] (the party of Prime Minister [[Mark Rutte]]), was filmed and circulated in the press.<ref name=\"Heftige\">{{cite news |title=Zien: heftige confrontatie krakers en bewoner |url=https://www.telegraaf.nl/video/2121500/zien-heftige-confrontatie-krakers-en-bewoner |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Telegraaf |date=4 June 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413071715/https://www.telegraaf.nl/video/2121500/zien-heftige-confrontatie-krakers-en-bewoner |archivedate=13 April 2019 |language=NL}}</ref><ref name=\"Break\">{{cite news |last1=Brown |first1=Emma |title=\u2018We Are Here\u2019 squatters stopped by residents when they try and break in (vid inside!) |url=https://dutchreview.com/news/dutch/we-are-here-squatters-stopped-by-residents-when-they-try-and-break-in-vid-inside/ |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=Dutch Review |date=5 June 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711171614/https://dutchreview.com/news/dutch/we-are-here-squatters-stopped-by-residents-when-they-try-and-break-in-vid-inside/ |archivedate=11 July 2019}}</ref> In April 2019, member of the collective Fortune M. was given a three-day jail sentence and a conditional fine of \u20ac150, for damaging a door during the attempt to squat the building.<ref name=\"Boete\">{{cite news |title=Celstraf en voorwaardelijke boete lid We Are Here |url=https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/celstraf-en-voorwaardelijke-boete-lid-we-are-here~b5a819f3/ |accessdate=10 May 2019 |work=Parool |agency=ANP |date=26 April 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510193818/https://www.parool.nl/amsterdam/celstraf-en-voorwaardelijke-boete-lid-we-are-here~b5a819f3/ |archivedate=10 May 2019 |quote=De politierechter in Amsterdam heeft de 36-jarige Fortune M., lid van het vluchtelingencollectief We Are Here, veroordeeld tot een celstraf van drie dagen en een voorwaardelijke geldboete van 150 euro.}}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\n* 2014: Photographer Manel Quiros won third place in the [[International Photography Awards]] with a photoseries following We Are Here.<ref name=\"IPA\">{{cite web |title=We Are Here |url=https://photoawards.com/winner/zoom.php?eid=8-135031-17 |website=International Photography Awards |accessdate=5 July 2019 |language=EN}}</ref>\n* 2015-2016: Inspired by meeting members of the We Are Here collective and following them around for several months, Dutch artist Manon van Hoeckel created the Limbo Embassy. This provided a way for people to hear the stories of We Are Here participants. It was also a means for them to earn money, important since they were otherwise not allowed to work or volunteer, but because it was an artistic project they could be paid for performances and sell political printed matter. Between June 2015 to June 2016, the embassy visited 15 events, including the [[Dutch Design Week]] in [[Eindhoven]].<ref name=\"Limbo\" /><ref name=\"Locals\">{{cite news |last1=Reimerink |first1=Letty |title=In Amsterdam, an 'Embassy' Where Migrants Connect With Locals |url=https://www.citylab.com/design/2015/09/in-amsterdam-an-embassy-where-migrants-connect-with-locals/406102/ |accessdate=11 July 2019 |work=City Lab |date=18 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711211530/https://www.citylab.com/design/2015/09/in-amsterdam-an-embassy-where-migrants-connect-with-locals/406102/ |archive-date=11 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* 2015: Alexandra Jansse made an hour long documentary called ''Wij Zijn Hier'' about the group <ref name=\"Hacks\">{{cite web |title=Hacks/Hackers Amsterdam is organizing a 'Refugee Hackathon' from February 4\u20136 at A-Lab. |url=http://hackshackers.nl/media/ |website=Hacks Hackers |accessdate=3 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830180058/http://hackshackers.nl/media/ |archive-date=30 August 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* 2017: We Are Here featured in the exhibition ''Architecture of Appropriation'' at [[Netherlands Architecture Institute|Het Nieuwe Instituut]] (the Dutch Institute of Architecture), in [[Rotterdam]].<ref name=\"RIBAJ\">{{cite web |last1=Buxton |first1=Pamela |title=Squatting as urban regeneration |url=https://www.ribaj.com/culture/architecture-of-appropriation |website=RIBAJ |accessdate=25 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525072658/https://www.ribaj.com/culture/architecture-of-appropriation |archive-date=25 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* 2018: Artist Hilda Moucharrafieh won the International Bursary Award at the Amsterdam Fringe Festival for her project ''Tracing Erased Memories: A parallel walk of Amsterdam & Cairo.'' She worked with members of We Are Here to make a choreographed roadmap in which a person walked through central Amsterdam wearing headphones and hearing the sounds of someone walking through central Cairo.<ref name=\"HKU\">{{cite news |title=Hilda Moucharrafieh wins the International Bursary Award |url=https://www.hku.nl/Home/Education/Masters/MAProgrammeScenography/NewsAndEvents/NewsAndEvents/HildaMoucharrafiehWinsTheInternationalBursaryAward.htm |accessdate=14 May 2019 |work=HKU |date=24 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514142026/https://www.hku.nl/Home/Education/Masters/MAProgrammeScenography/NewsAndEvents/NewsAndEvents/HildaMoucharrafiehWinsTheInternationalBursaryAward.htm |archive-date=14 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* 2018: Academics who have studied We Are Here organised a meeting at Spui 25 cultural centre to discuss their findings with members of the collective and to listen to their feedback.<ref name=\"Idzikowska\">{{cite web |last1=Idzikowska |first1=Ula |title=Wat leert de wetenschap ons over We Are Here? |url=https://www.oneworld.nl/movement/welke-lessen-leert-de-wetenschap-ons-over-we-are-here/ |website=One World |accessdate=5 July 2019 |date=2018-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190703154441/https://www.oneworld.nl/movement/welke-lessen-leert-de-wetenschap-ons-over-we-are-here/ |archive-date=3 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Abahlali baseMjondolo]]\n*[[Calais Jungle]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Spijkerboer, Thomas (2013) ''\u201cWij zijn hier\u201d. Gelijke behandeling van niet uitzetbare vreemdelingen?'' [http://dare.ubvu.vu.nl/bitstream/handle/1871/40177/Artikel?sequence=1 Artikel 1 lezing] (pdf in Dutch)\n*Slingenberg, Lieneke & Bonneau, Louise (2017) [https://brill.com/view/journals/emil/19/4/article-p335_335.xml?lang=en (In)formal Migrant Settlements and Right to Respect for a Home] in ''European Journal of Migration and Law'' Vol 19:4 pp335\u2013369 10.1163/15718166-12340013\n*Truijen, K. (2019) ''Architecture of Appropriation - On Squatting as Spatial Practice'' {{ISBN|9789083015200}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://wijzijnhier.org Official website]\n* [http://wijzijnhier.org/tijdslijn/geschiedenis-van-wij-zijn-hier/ Timeline of events up to mid 2015]\n\n{{Squatting}}\n{{SquatNL}}\n\n[[Category:Squatters' movements]]\n[[Category:Squatting in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:European migrant crisis]]\n[[Category:Amsterdam]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in the Netherlands]]\n", "name_user": "Mujinga", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBackground", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/We_Are_Here_(collective)"}
{"title_page": "List of Pretty Little Liars characters", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Pretty Little Liars'' characters}}\n{{update|inaccurate=yes|date=August 2017}}\n''[[Pretty Little Liars]]'' is an [[Television in the United States|American]] [[teen drama]] [[television series]] created by [[I. Marlene King]] for [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]]. It is based on [[Sara Shepard]]'s [[Pretty Little Liars (book series)|novel series of the same name]]. Below is a list consisting of the many characters who have appeared throughout the series' seven-season run.\n{{TOC limit|2}}\n\n==Overview==\nThe following table contains an overall look on the main, recurring and guest characters. The recurring and guest characters, marked in red and blue, respectively, have appeared in more than five episodes in the respective season they are pointed out. The main characters, marked in green, are those whose portrayer has had received [[ensemble cast]] [[Billing (filmmaking)|billing]] in at least one episode in the season they are denoted.\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:85%; width:auto\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Character\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Portrayed by\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"8\" | Appearances\n|-\n!First\n! scope=\"col\" | [[Pretty Little Liars (season 1)|Season 1]]\n! scope=\"col\" | [[Pretty Little Liars (season 2)|Season 2]]\n! scope=\"col\" | [[Pretty Little Liars (season 3)|Season 3]]\n! scope=\"col\" | [[Pretty Little Liars (season 4)|Season 4]]\n! scope=\"col\" | [[Pretty Little Liars (season 5)|Season 5]]\n! scope=\"col\" | [[Pretty Little Liars (season 6)|Season 6]]\n! scope=\"col\" | [[Pretty Little Liars (season 7)|Season 7]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"10\" style=\"background-color:#ccccff;\" | Main characters\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[#Spencer Hastings|Spencer Hastings]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Troian Bellisario]]\n| \"Pilot\" \n| 